# Code Artifact: .gitignore
# Description: Keeps local build products, editor caches, and verification scratch folders out of source control.
# Programmer: HudLink development team (Brandon Dodge, Zach Sevart, Asa Maker, Jonathan Gott, Josh Dwoskin)
# Date Created: 2026-04-26
# Revision History:
# - 2026-04-26 - HudLink development team - Added ignore rules after local Android build verification.
# Preconditions: Git reads this file from the repository root.
# Acceptable Inputs: Git ignore patterns for generated files, local caches, and machine-specific folders.
# Unacceptable Inputs: Patterns that hide source files, sprint documents, project settings, or release artifacts that should be reviewed.
# Postconditions: Local build caches and generated outputs do not appear as untracked release changes.
# Return Values: Git ignore files do not return values; Git consumes the patterns when showing status or staging files.
# Error and Exception Conditions: Bad patterns can accidentally hide files, so source folders are not ignored here.
# Side Effects: Changes how Git reports local generated files.
# Invariants: Team-owned source, documents, and build scripts remain visible to Git.
# Known Faults: Existing tracked generated files remain tracked until the team explicitly removes them.
# Major Blocks: Root-level cache rules come first, followed by Android and Unity generated folders.
# Line Comments: Each group has a short heading so the ignore intent is clear.

# Local verification homes used when Gradle cannot write to user profile folders.
.gradle-home/
.android-home/

# Android and Gradle generated output.
android/.gradle/
android/**/build/

# Unity generated output and local editor state.
Unity/Library/
Unity/Logs/
Unity/Temp/
Unity/Obj/
Unity/Build/
Unity/Builds/
Unity/UserSettings/
